          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_014WRg2ZX1r44bMWA6fuu7Pw\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_014WRg2ZX1r44bMWA6fuu7Pw\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Got it! Now let's talk about your solution. How does Friend of the Pod solve the pain points for podcast hosts and guests?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Our AI matches hosts with guests based on topic expertise, audience size, and availability—no more endless cold emails\\\",\\n    \\\"We provide a vetted database of guests with verified credentials, so hosts know they're booking quality people\\\",\\n    \\\"Guests create one profile and get matched with multiple relevant shows automatically, saving them weeks of outreach\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What makes your matchmaking process effective and different from hosts just searching LinkedIn or Twitter?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01HZd7xExKLnK7DojChpZKGe\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01HZd7xExKLnK7DojChpZKGe\"}]}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n  You are a helpful marketing consultant who helps users test their business ideas.\\n      The process consists of 3 steps:\\n      1. Brainstorm a killer new business idea\\n      2. Design a landing page with killer marketing copy\\n      3. Launch an ads campaign to drive traffic — and see if people are excited to buy!\\n</background>\\n\\n<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n      business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n\\n              You've been enlisted to lead this brainstorming session.\\n</role>\\n\\n<rules_for_brainstorming>\\n  1. You are encouraging and help users find the best angle. You only push back on ideas that are genuinely unclear or lack any differentiation—not on ideas that are simply \\\"good\\\" vs \\\"great.\\\"\\n              2. You have a reputation to uphold. You won't accept a bad business idea, but will help the user find a better angle.\\n              3. If the user is struggling, you can find creative angles to answer a question.\\n              4. Save answers when they're solid and actionable. Don't chase perfection—a clear, differentiated idea is enough. Ask ONE follow-up at most per topic, then move on.\\n</rules_for_brainstorming>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Help the user brainstorm marketing copy for their landing page.\\n              Guide them through each question until you have enough context to generate effective marketing copy.\\n</task>\\n\\n<be_generous important=\\\"read this carefully\\\">\\n  You have a tendency to over-refine. Fight this instinct.\\n              \\n              A response is GOOD ENOUGH if it:\\n              - Explains what the business does\\n              - Has at least one differentiator\\n              - Is specific enough to write copy about\\n              \\n              Do NOT ask for clarification if:\\n              - The user has given 2+ sentences of detail\\n              - There's a clear value proposition\\n              - You could already write a headline from their answer\\n              \\n              The user's example answer has ALL THREE. Save it and move on.\\n</be_generous>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. If the user has answered any topics with a solid response, call the save_answers tool - do NOT forget to save answers when we have them! \\n              2. If the user has SKIPPED a topic, do not call save_answers for the skipped topics\\n              3. Then, if:\\n                 - The user has answered all topics, output finishBrainstorming\\n                 - OTHERWISE, ask the next question, following the output_format_rules\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<important>\\n  Do not miss anything important the user said! Any important\\n              business context they give you should be saved to the answers.\\n</important>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  socialProof\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<users_last_message important=\\\"this is what you should focus on. did they answer the current topic of socialProof? did they give you a great response?\\\">\\n  Skip\\n</users_last_message>\\n\\n<skippable>\\n  topic is skippable\\n</skippable>\\n\\n<skipped_topics important=\\\"this is the list of topics that have been skipped, don't bother asking about them\\\">\\n  audience, solution\\n</skipped_topics>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  IMPORTANT: Your response MUST be in this exact format:\\n\\n              {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Brief intro to the question\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\", \\\"Example 3\\\"], // Optional\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Restate what you're asking for\\\" // Optional\\n              }\\n\\n              You MUST output valid JSON in this format.\\n</output_format_rules>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1011,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1011,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\",\"id\":\"msg_01KBGKBnPpF8SfYTTNSkKLGm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"No problem! Let's talk about social proof. Do you have any testimonials, credentials, or background that would build trust with potential customers?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"I've been a podcast host for 5 years and booked 200+ guests—I know this pain firsthand\\\",\\n    \\\"We've already matched 50+ successful podcast episodes in our beta\\\",\\n    \\\"I worked at a talent booking agency and saw how broken the manual process was\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What would make podcast hosts and guests trust that you can deliver great matches?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2911,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":150,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
