            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2790,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\",\"id\":\"msg_01AuAAFCjmywHpS3sRQyRKCA\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01XXzPpys7KEtmeHLmaCE8MC\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"Our primary audience is podcast hosts who produce interview-style shows and need a steady stream of quality guests. These are typically independent podcasters or small production teams (1-3 people) who handle booking themselves. They're passionate about their content but frustrated by the time-consuming guest research and outreach process - often spending 5-10 hours per week just to book a few guests. They want to maintain high content quality and consistent publishing schedules, but the manual booking process creates bottlenecks that lead to missed episodes or last-minute scrambling. Current solutions like cold LinkedIn outreach or generic booking agencies either take too much time or don't understand their niche well enough to find the right fit.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the time-consuming guest discovery problem by using AI-powered filtering to match podcast hosts with ideal guests in minutes instead of hours. Our platform analyzes both the podcast's content, audience, and style alongside potential guests' expertise, speaking topics, and media presence to surface highly relevant matches. Hosts simply input their episode topic or guest criteria, and our system instantly provides a curated list of pre-vetted guests who are actively seeking podcast appearances. The result: hosts go from spending 5-10 hours per week on guest research and cold outreach to booking quality guests in under 30 minutes, allowing them to focus on content creation and maintain consistent publishing schedules without sacrificing guest quality.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"As podcast producers ourselves, we've experienced firsthand the frustration of spending entire afternoons hunting for the perfect guest, only to get ghosted or find poor fits. After helping dozens of podcaster friends streamline their booking process, we built Friend of the Pod to solve this at scale. Our beta users are already saving an average of 8 hours per week on guest booking, with one host telling us they went from booking 2 guests per month to 8 guests per month with better topic alignment. We're the only platform purpose-built for two-sided podcast matchmaking, and we've facilitated over 500 successful podcast interviews in our first six months.\"}]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2679,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":551,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
