          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Y7M4L2rzjScMTvYjaJf5Xu\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"idea\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service. We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure, and we're the only platform that does this at scale. We solve the 'needle in a haystack' problem: hosts spend hours finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Y7M4L2rzjScMTvYjaJf5Xu\"}]},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Got it, skipping audience. Now let's talk about your solution. How exactly does Friend of the Pod solve the problem for podcast hosts? Walk me through what happens when someone uses your service.\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Hosts fill out a quick form about their show and ideal guest, then our AI matches them with vetted guests in 24 hours\\\",\\n    \\\"We use AI to analyze podcast topics and guest expertise, then surface the top 5 matches with booking links\\\",\\n    \\\"Hosts browse our database of pre-screened guests filtered by niche, experience level, and availability\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What's the actual process or mechanism that makes the magic happen?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n  The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n      We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n</background>\\n\\n<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n      business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<context>\\n  The user skipped 1 questions during the brainstorm.\\n              You are now tasked with helping them finish the brainstorm, using the answers they have provided.\\n</context>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n</role>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Create plausible answers for the skipped topics based on the answers the user has provided.\\n\\n              Do not invent answers or make things up. Use the information provided to create realistic answers.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"audience\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\\n\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\",\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\",\\n    \\\"socialProof\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\\n\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\\nFriend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\\nOver 10k creators use Friend of the Pod to find guests for their shows.\\\\n    Real case: Host found 3 guests in 10 minutes instead of 5 hours of manual outreach, leading to 2 viral episodes. As the founder of the company, I used to work at Spotify and Apple Podcasts, so I've seen first hand what makes a guest a good fit for a show, and I understand the industry.\\\",\\n    \\\"solution\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\\n\\\\n        My target audience is podcast hosts with large audiences.\\\\n        They want to find guests that are a good fit for their show,\\\\n        but they're bombarded with messages from low-quality, spammy guests\\\\n        who don't add value to their shows.\\\\n    \\\\nFriend of the Pod has over 100+ filters to find the perfect guest for your show.\\\\n                We use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                We also use AI to match hosts and guests based on their content, audience, and goals.\\\\n                But what sets us apart is that we've trained proprietary models on messages that \\\\n                successful podcast hosts receive. We use this data to filter out pitches that \\\\n                are predicted to not be a good fit for your show.\\\\n            \\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\nThe target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\n\\n          TOPIC: Target Audience\\n\\nThe user needs help describing who their ideal customer is and what problems they face.\\n\\nSPECIFIC GUIDANCE FOR THIS TOPIC:\\n\\n- Break this into 3-4 clear sub-questions\\n- Sub-questions should build logically: WHO → PROBLEMS → GOALS → (optionally) WHY EXISTING SOLUTIONS FAIL\\n- Each sub-question should have a bold header and bracketed guidance\\n- Help them get specific about demographics AND psychographics\\n- Emphasize connecting problems to goals (they're two sides of same coin)\\n\\nSUB-QUESTIONS TO INCLUDE:\\n\\n1. **Who are they?** - Demographics, role, life context\\n2. **What problems do they face?** - Pain points, frustrations, obstacles\\n3. **What are they trying to achieve?** - Goals, desired outcomes, aspirations\\n4. (Optional) **Why don't current solutions work?** - Gap in market\\n\\nEXAMPLE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n- Should paint a vivid picture of a real person\\n- Must show clear connection between their problems and goals\\n- Problems should be specific, not generic (\\\"overwhelmed by too much to do\\\")\\n- Should help them see the emotional dimension, not just functional\\n\\nBAD EXAMPLE: \\\"Busy professionals who want to save time\\\"\\nGOOD EXAMPLE: \\\"Marketing managers at 10-50 person SaaS companies who are stretched thin managing multiple channels, feel guilty about inconsistent posting, and want to build thought leadership but can't justify hiring a full-time content person.\\\"\\n<task>\\n  Provide a clear, fill-in-the-blank template that helps them articulate their answer with specificity and clarity.\\n</task>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. Call the save_answers tool with the answers you have created for the skipped topics.\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  Do not output any text. Call the save_answers tool with the answers you have created for the skipped topics.\\n</output_format_rules>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
